  "body": "Continuation of #3460.\r\n\r\nWhen the `merge` hardfork is enabled, block rewards are not assigned to the coinbase address. This seems to be an expected behavior from ethereumjs, but I'm not sure if the Hardhat network should do that.\r\n\r\nSome things to check:\r\n\r\n- What does `geth --dev` do?\r\n- What does revm do?\r\n- How hard is to do this with ethereumjs? If it's too hard and we want to implement this, should we wait for rethnet?\r\n\r\ncc @alcuadrado",
